00:00:04.440 --> 00:00:06.708
Welcome to the first
module, which is dedicated

1
00:00:06.719 --> 00:00:07.579
to nasal breathing.

2
00:00:08.300 --> 00:00:10.428
Nasal breathing is absolutely
essential for healthy

3
00:00:10.439 --> 00:00:13.048
development, because if a
child breathes through their

4
00:00:13.059 --> 00:00:15.688
mouth, they will suffer
from frequent and persistent

5
00:00:15.699 --> 00:00:16.639
respiratory colds.

6
00:00:17.320 --> 00:00:19.708
Their upper lip will lift,
their front teeth will spread

7
00:00:19.719 --> 00:00:22.428
apart, and their overall
dental bite will undergo

8
00:00:22.439 --> 00:00:25.329
significant changes, which
can later lead to serious

9
00:00:25.340 --> 00:00:27.399
and potentially irreversible
health consequences.

10
00:00:28.300 --> 00:00:30.928
That's why at an early stage,
it's important to teach

11
00:00:30.939 --> 00:00:32.399
a child to breathe
through their nose.

12
00:00:33.040 --> 00:00:36.408
And today, in this lesson,
we will achieve this

13
00:00:36.419 --> 00:00:38.459
through engaging and
playful activities.

